#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:1
msgid "Add spatio-temporal harmonics filter/source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:3
msgid "Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:5
msgid ""
"You can now use a new filter to compute spatio-temporal harmonics on each "
"point of your input dataset. This avoids some manual computation through the "
"calculator which would be hard to follow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:10
msgid ""
"This filter allows you to add multiple harmonics defined by their amplitude, "
"temporal frequency, wave vector, and phase. The sum of them will be computed "
"using the sinus function for each point. Note that there is no cosinus in "
"this function. If no harmonic is specified, values will be null."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:17
msgid "Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:19
msgid ""
"You can now generate an image data with harmonics data. This new source "
"allows you to specify the uniform grid extent. It also lets you choose the "
"harmonics you want, the same way as in the filter (it is embedded). Finally, "
"it can generate time steps by specifying time values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:25
msgid ""
"If no harmonic is specified, the source will generate null harmonic values. "
"You can generate default harmonics with the `ResetHarmonics` function though."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-harmonics-filter-source.md:29
msgid ""
"If no time value is specified, the source will not generate time steps. You "
"can generate default ones with the reset `ResetTimeStepValues` function "
"though."
msgstr ""

